# Migration Walkthrough: Azure to Standard OpenAI

## Overview
We have successfully migrated the backend from **Azure AI Foundry** to **Standard OpenAI** to support the `gpt-5.1-2025-11-13` model.

## key Changes
1.  **Backend Configuration**:
    -   Updated [.env](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/.env) with `OPENAI_API_KEY` and `OPENAI_MODEL`.
    -   Refactored [src/backend/agents.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/backend/agents.py) to use [OpenAIChatClient](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/external/agent-framework/python/packages/core/agent_framework/openai/_chat_client.py#472-559) (Standard) correctly passing `model_id`.
2.  **Product Documentation**:
    -   Updated [NextstepPRD.md](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/NextstepPRD.md) to reflect the new technical stack (Standard OpenAI).

## Verification Results

### 1. API-   **WebSocket Safety**: [ChatInterface](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/frontend/components/ChatInterface.tsx#14-175) now includes **Auto-Reconnect** logic. If the server restarts, the UI will display "Reconnecting..." until service is restored, preventing crashes.
-   **WebSocket Safety**: [ChatInterface](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/frontend/components/ChatInterface.tsx#14-175) now includes **Auto-Reconnect** logic. If the server restarts, the UI will display "Reconnecting..." until service is restored, preventing crashes.
-   **Zero Latency Boot**: Refactored [main.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/backend/main.py) to use a [lifespan](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/backend/main.py#14-25) manager (Global Orchestrator) for robust startup. This eliminates connection latency while ensuring failure resilience.

