## Debugging Round 3: Connection Stability & Routing (Verified)

### Issues Resolved
1.  **Peer Closed Connection / Timeout**:
    *   **Cause**: Large queries (like "Explain MCP") took longer than the default 30s timeout, causing the client to disconnect mid-stream.
    *   **Fix**: Increased `AsyncOpenAI` client timeout to **300 seconds** (5 minutes) in [src/backend/agents.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/backend/agents.py).
2.  **"Text Dump" instead of Graph**:
    *   **Cause**: The router sent "explain" queries to the Chat workflow (text only).
    *   **Fix**: Added keywords `["explain", "concepts", "understand"]` to the router in [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/backend/orchestrator.py) to target the **Canvas Agent**.

### Verification
*   **Routing**: Confirmed "explain MCP" now routes to Canvas Mode.
*   **Stability**: Verified `AsyncOpenAI` initialization with new timeout settings accepts requests (HTTP 200 OK).

### 3. "Reconnecting..." Phantom Disconnect
*   **Cause**: Long inference times (thinking) caused the WebSocket to stay silent, triggering browser/network timeout.
*   **Fix**: Implemented a **Heartbeat** in [orchestrator.py](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/src/backend/orchestrator.py) that sends a [ping](file:///c:/Users/ADMIN/Desktop/nextstep-ver3/external/agent-framework/python/packages/core/agent_framework/_types.py#3208-3219) every 2 seconds if the backend is busy. This keeps the connection alive.
